Downloads the KSGP (Karst, Silva, GTDB, and PR2) reference database for
SSU rRNA taxonomic assignment, particularly optimized for Archaea
communities. KSGP combines near full-length rRNA sequences from Karst
et al. 2018, re-annotated SILVA prokaryote SSU sequences, cleaned GTDB 16S
sequences, PR2 eukaryote 18S sequences, and MIDORI2 mitochondrial
sequences. Taxonomy is based on GTDB, providing phylogenetically consistent
classification.

Also provides access to the GTDB+ and GTDB_cleaned databases built as
intermediate steps during KSGP construction.

Three annotation variants are available for \code{database = "KSGP"} and
\code{file_type = "tax"}:
\itemize{
\item \code{"sintax"} (default): SINTAX-based taxonomic assignments (KSGP Sintax
in the paper). Available for all versions.
\item \code{"lca"}: Conservative lowest common ancestor assignments (KSGP LCA).
Only available for version \code{"3.1"}.
\item \code{"ksgp_plus"}: Similarity-clustered putative taxa (KSGP+). Only
available for version \code{"3.1"}.
}
}
\details{
When \code{file_type = "fasta"}, the function downloads the matching
\verb{KSGP_v<version>.tar.gz} archive (one HTTP request) and extracts the
FASTA — and, when \code{tax_format != "none"}, the chosen \code{.tax} file — to
\code{dest_dir}, then removes the archive. The archive is roughly 3.5x
smaller than the raw FASTA (e.g. ~686 MB vs ~2.4 GB for v3.1), so
this is both faster and lighter on the server than two separate
requests. The KSGP FASTA and taxonomy files are otherwise separate
downloads.

With \code{tax_format = "sintax"} (or \code{"dada2"}), the taxonomy is merged
into the FASTA headers (one sequence ID per row, matched against the
\code{.tax} file) and the \code{.tax} file is removed, so the result is a
single FASTA ready for VSEARCH/dada2 — the original prefix letters
from the \code{.tax} are preserved in the SINTAX output (a KSGP line
starting with \code{k__Bacteria;} becomes \verb{>ID;tax=k:Bacteria,...},
not \verb{d:Bacteria,...}). To use KSGP for taxonomic assignment:
\itemize{
\item With VSEARCH SINTAX: download the FASTA (\code{file_type = "fasta"},
\code{tax_format = "sintax"}).
\item With dada2: download the FASTA (\code{file_type = "fasta"},
\code{tax_format = "dada2"}).
\item With LotuS2: the KSGP database is integrated directly.
\item For a complete set of all files: use \code{file_type = "archive"}.
}

KSGP substantially improves Archaea annotation over SILVA and Greengenes2:
Class and Order assignments increase by 2.7x and 4.2x respectively.

Please cite: Grant A et al. (2025) KSGP 3.1: improved taxonomic annotation
of Archaea communities using LotuS2, the genome taxonomy database and
RNAseq data. ISME Communications 5(1): ycaf094.
\doi{10.1093/ismeco/ycaf094}
